#, php-format
msgid ""
"We wished to keep our \"<a href=\"%s\">Restrictions</a>\" page short, so we "
"moved many of the license restrictions out here. Here is the fine print "
"inside the Microsoft licenses."
msgstr ""
"我們希望讓這份〈<a href=\"%s\">限制</a>〉頁面儘可能簡短，所以我們把大多數的授"
"權條款限制移到這裡來。這些是微軟授權條款的完整細節。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:26
msgid "It is unclear who can use, receive or buy your software."
msgstr "授權條款對於誰可以使用、收受、或是購買你的軟體並沒有說明清楚。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:28
msgid ""
"The license is particularly unclear as to who may or may not use your "
"version of Windows or Office. Several sentences in the Microsoft Office "
"license suggest it would be illegal to let your neighbour type a letter with "
"your version of Word on your computer."
msgstr ""
"這個授權條款尤其在說明誰可以使用、或不可以使用你的 Windows 或 Office 時更含混"
"不清。微軟 Office 授權條款中的幾句話暗示若你的鄰居使用你電腦上的 Office 來寫"
"一封信是違法的。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:30
msgid ""
"It is however clear in the Microsoft Windows license that you may <em>only</"
"em> give or sell your copy of Windows software to anyone <strong>if you are "
"the first buyer</strong>. This means, that if you buy it from the user who "
"initially purchased it from Microsoft, then <em>you</em> are not able to "
"sell or give the software away to yet another user, even if you do not use "
"it anymore, even if you buy the latest software version with your new "
"computer."
msgstr ""
"然而，微軟 Windows 的授權條款中指明<em>只有</em>在<strong>你是這份 Windows 授"
"權的第一任買主</strong>的情況下，你才可以將你所購買的 Windows 軟體副本轉送或"
"販賣給其他人。這也就意味著，如果你的 Windows 是從其他已經向微軟購買過這份軟體"
"的人買來的，或是作業系統是預裝在電腦中，那麼<em>你</em>就無法再轉賣或轉送給其"
"他人，即使你已經不再使用它，甚至你也為新電腦買了之後的軟體版本也是一樣。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:34
msgid ""
"You may not lease, lend or provide commercial hosting services with the "
"software"
msgstr "你不能出租、出借這套軟體，或是用它來進行商業代管服務"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:36
msgid ""
"You cannot let professional users use your software, whether they pay for "
"the service or not, and whether you use a &quot;Professional&quot; license "
"or not."
msgstr ""
"你不能讓其他專業人士使用你購買的軟體，無論他們是否購買過，也不論你是否購買的"
"是不是「專業版」(Professional) 授權。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:40
msgid "The upgrade is only valid for the first license you use it on"
msgstr "你只能在第一臺使用這份軟體授權的機器上升級作業系統"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:42
msgid ""
"If that original license expires (for example because the computer it came "
"on stops working), so does the upgrade. If you purchase an upgrade, you are "
"not allowed to use the original software version anymore."
msgstr ""
"如果你原來的授權失效 (例如：你的電腦壞了停止運作)，那麼你也將失去你的作業系統"
"升級資格。如果你購買了升級版並升級，那麼就再也不能使用原來的舊版軟體。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:46
msgid "Educational versions are crippled"
msgstr "殘廢的教育版"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:48
msgid ""
"If Microsoft accepts to define you as a student or an academic, you are "
"allowed to buy an academic license, and install the software on three "
"computers. But it is illegal to use it for any commercial purpose \"<em>or "
"in any way related to the operation of any business enterprise or revenue-"
"generating activities</em>\"."
msgstr ""
"如果微軟承認你是位學生或是研究學者，你才會被允許購買教育學術授權，並安裝到最"
"多 3 臺電腦上。但任何商業用途、「<em>或是一切與營利企業或營收行為相關之活動</"
"em>」都是違法的。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:52
msgid "The components of the software may not be separated"
msgstr "軟體組件不能分離"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:54
msgid ""
"It is illegal to buy Microsoft Office, then install only Word on one "
"computer, and only Excel on another. The Office suite is one single product."
msgstr ""
"購買微軟 Office，然後在一臺電腦上只安裝 Word、另外一臺電腦上只安裝 Excel，那"
"麼你可能會被告上法院。微軟的辦公套裝軟體是一個單一產品。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:58
msgid "Private information is collected"
msgstr "收集隱私資訊"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:60
msgid ""
"The licence explicitly states that \"Microsoft and its affiliates\" collect "
"technical information gathered on your computer by the software. They "
"\"<em>may use this information solely to improve products or to provide "
"customized services or technologies</em>\"."
msgstr ""
"授權條款上明載：「微軟及其分支機構」可以透過你的電腦來收集技術資訊。他們"
"「<em>僅將此類資訊用於改進產品，及提供個人化的服務或技術支援</em>」。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:62
msgid ""
"In order to activate most Microsoft products, as part of the license "
"agreement, your computer connects to the Microsoft servers and sends &quot;"
"technical&quot; information. It can &quot;solely&quot; be used for pretty "
"much anything."
msgstr ""
"授權條款的其中一部份提到，若要啟動微軟的產品，你的電腦必須連接到微軟的伺服器"
"並送出「技術」資訊。這些資訊「僅只」會用在許多事情上。"

#. translators: If it exists, please use a non-official translation of the GPL in your language, as pointed on http://www.gnu.org/licenses/translations.html
#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:72
msgid "http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html"
msgstr "http://www.linux.org.tw/CLDP/OLD/doc/GPL.html"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:72
msgid "The GNU General Public License"
msgstr "GNU 通用公眾授權條款"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:72
msgid "The GPL"
msgstr "GPL"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:74
msgid ""
"The GNU General Public License, under which GNU/Linux and a vast amount of "
"free software are published."
msgstr "GNU 通用公眾授權條款，GNU/Linux 及大量自由軟體採用的發行條款。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:76
msgid "Comparing the GPL to the Microsoft WinXP License"
msgstr "GPL 與 Microsoft WinXP License 條款的比較"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:78
msgid ""
"A thorough and clear comparison of the <abbr title=\"GNU General Public "
"License\">GPL</abbr> and the Microsoft <abbr title=\"End-User License "
"Agreement\">EULA</abbr> license that governs the use of most Windows XP "
"versions."
msgstr ""
"一份完整且清楚的 <abbr title=\"GNU General Public License\">GPL</abbr> 與微"
"軟 <abbr title=\"End-User License Agreement\">EULA</abbr> 授權條款 (被用於大"
"多數的 Windows XP 系統上) 的比較。"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:81
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:137
msgid "http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/right-to-read.html"
msgstr "http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/right-to-read.html"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:81
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:137
msgid "The Right to Read"
msgstr "閱讀的權利"

#: lib/views/windows.restrictions.further_details.php:83
msgid ""
"A short story by Richard Stallman that describes what influence restrictive "
"licenses could have on our lives."
msgstr ""
"一份由理查·斯托曼 (Richard Stallman) 所編寫的小故事，闡述了受限制的授權條款對"
"我們生活的影響。"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:20
msgid "What about source code?"
msgstr "來源程式碼怎麼了？"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:23
msgid ""
"The source code details the way a program works (it is effectively what "
"programmers write). Without it no one can understand how the software is "
"built."
msgstr ""
"來源程式碼是一個程式如何運作的細節（這是程式設計師實際上在寫的東西）。沒有來"
"源程式碼就沒有人能夠了解一個軟體是如何被建構出來的。"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:24
msgid ""
"It does not matter if you can't read code: whether or not it is available "
"<strong>directly affects any user</strong>."
msgstr ""
"你是否能讀懂源始碼並不重要：它是否公開<strong>直接影響了所有使用者</strong>。"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:32
msgid "No one can look inside"
msgstr "沒有人能瞭解內部"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:34
msgid ""
"Windows comes without its source code. More than that: all users must abide "
"to the license term that says:"
msgstr ""
"Windows 的軟體並沒有隨著它的來源程式碼一起提供。更糟的是：所有 Windows 的使用"
"者都必須遵從下列的這個授權條款："

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:36
msgid "You may not reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the software."
msgstr "你不得對此軟體進行逆向工程，反編譯，或是反組譯此軟體。"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:38
msgid ""
"As such, it is illegal to work out how Windows or Microsoft Word are "
"designed. It is even illegal to try. You are also forbidden to modify the "
"program for any purpose."
msgstr ""
"正因為這樣，研究出 Windows 或者微軟 Office 是如何設計的是非法的，甚至只是嘗試"
"也是非法的。以任何目的去修改程式也是被嚴格禁止的。"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:40
msgid ""
"This restriction in the license makes sure that <strong>Microsoft remain the "
"sole organisation that understand how their products work</strong>. Windows "
"is very much like a car that only the original manufacturer is allowed to "
"service."
msgstr ""
"這份授權條款的限制確保了 <strong>微軟是唯一一個能夠瞭解他們產品如何工作的組織"
"</strong>。Windows 非常像一部只能由生產廠商維修的汽車。"

#. translators: This is the quote from Stallman at the start of the article.
#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:46
msgid ""
"You might say, \"How do I change this recipe to take out the salt?\" and the "
"great chef would respond, \"How dare you insult my recipe, the child of my "
"brain and my palate, by trying to tamper with it? You don't have the "
"judgment to change my recipe and make it work right!\""
msgstr ""
"你可能會說：「我可不可以不要按照你的食譜加鹽？」然後他們偉大的主廚可能會說："
"「你怎麼敢玩弄我的作品，修改我偉大的食譜，侮辱我智慧的結晶！你不能判定我的作"
"品成功與否！」"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:47
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:156
msgid "http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/why-free.html"
msgstr "http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/why-free.html"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:47
msgid "Why Software Should Be Free"
msgstr "為什麼軟體應該自由"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:54
msgid "You can trust free software"
msgstr "你可以信任自由軟體"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:56
msgid ""
"It comes as no surprise that proprietary software is severely lacking in "
"terms of security, compared to software whose source code is freely "
"available (including GNU/Linux)."
msgstr ""
"相較於來源程式碼對外開放自由存取的軟體（包含 GNU/Linux 作業系統），專有軟體在"
"安全性方面有許多的缺陷並不那麼的令人驚訝。"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:58
msgid ""
"Free software means <strong>programmers can change the code</strong> to "
"repair flaws. It means you can hire someone to really check how secure your "
"software is. It means you can benefit from the contributions of a world-wide "
"community to improve safety and reliability. Fifteen million users run GNU/"
"Linux without an anti-virus, in complete safety. And the servers behind "
"search engines and banks run on it too."
msgstr ""
"自由軟體意味著<strong>程式設計師可以通過修改來源程式碼</strong>來修復缺陷。也"
"就意味著你可以雇用一個人來檢查你使用的軟體有多安全。也就意味著你可以獲得來自"
"全球無數社群的無數開發者給你帶來的安全和可靠性。一千五百萬的使用者執行 GNU/"
"Linux，卻基本上沒有使用防毒軟體，因為他們知道他們處於安全之中。搜索引擎等網站"
"的伺服器、銀行的伺服器也有許多是執行它的。"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:64
msgid ""
"Source code is the recipe for software. How could one improve on a meal with "
"too much salt, if forbidden to look at the recipe used to cook it?"
msgstr ""
"來源程式碼是軟體的食譜。如果一個人被禁止看做某道菜的食譜，又該如何改善加了太"
"多鹽的那道菜的口味呢？"

#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:66
msgid ""
"Using Windows and Office requires us to <strong>not ask</strong> nor search "
"for the source of the software. Only Microsoft developers can modify your "
"program."
msgstr ""
"如果你使用了 Windows 和 Office，你只能對其源始碼<strong>不聞不問</strong>。只"
"有微軟的開發者可以修改你購買的軟體。"

#. translators: Please note the conditionnal tense: we try to not be too harsh on the reader here ;-)
#: lib/views/windows.what_about_source_code.php:70
msgid ""
"Which would you rather trust: the package you are forbidden to study, or the "
"package with the recipe?"
msgstr "你更願意相信哪一個呢？你不能學習參考的軟體，或者告訴你一切細節的軟體？"

#. translators: use the definition of "free software" on GNU.org in place of softwareliberty.com
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:24
msgid ""
"Five misconceptions about <a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\">free "
"software</a>, corrected."
msgstr ""
"對<a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\">自由軟體</a>的五個誤解及觀念更"
"正。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:27
msgid ""
"1. The software industry can't keep going if programmers don't get paid."
msgstr "1. 如果程式設計師沒有得到金錢報酬軟體產業就無法正常發展"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:29
msgid ""
"Let's begin with one simple fact: free software programmers <em>do</em> like "
"to get paid, and all need to buy lunch at some time."
msgstr ""
"咱們講句實在話：自由軟體開發者們<em>樂意</em>收到金錢酬勞，畢竟大家都必須要餬"
"口飯吃。"

#. translators: Here, the %s placeholder simply puts a link to a footnote in this page
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:32
#, php-format
msgid ""
"When we mention free software, we refer to <strong>liberty not price</"
"strong>. You may actually pay to get free software (or \"open source\" "
"software %s), which you can then study, change and copy at will."
msgstr ""
"當我們提到自由軟體時，我們的重點是在於<strong>自由而不是免費</strong>。事實上"
"你也可以花錢買自由軟體 (或是「開源」軟體 %s)，也可以研究、修改和複製。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:34
msgid ""
"How does it work? You can think about it the following way: software is just "
"code, code is only math. Once you view software as <strong>useful math</"
"strong>, an elaborate language, not like ordinary property, there is no "
"reason to restrict others' use of it."
msgstr ""
"此話怎說呢？基本上你可以這麼想：軟體就是程式碼，程式碼就像是數學式，像是"
"<strong>具有實用性的數學式</strong>，它是一種精心設計的語言，而不像是普通的私"
"有財產，所以沒有理由去限制人們使用它的權利。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:35
msgid ""
"Just like math (where nobody would claim property on an equation), software "
"requires advanced knowledge to be adapted, improved, applied correctly. This "
"is where programmers generally generate an income: many customers, "
"especially companies, are willing to pay for regular security updates and "
"improvements on software."
msgstr ""
"就像是數學一樣，沒有人能夠對一個數學公式註冊專利，而軟體需要相當進階的專業知"
"識才能夠正確地調適、改進與使用，這就是程式設計師可以藉以謀取利潤的空間，有許"
"多客戶(尤其是企業級客戶)都相當樂意花錢請人來對軟體進行安全性更新以及功能改"
"良。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:36
msgid ""
"Free software companies benefit from a very decentralised development system "
"with a large number of voluntary contributors. The revenues inside the free "
"software industry might be smaller than in the proprietary counterpoint, but "
"are by no means negligible. In the end, individual users generally end up "
"using free software at no cost."
msgstr ""
"自由軟體公司接收了非常大量且分散的自願性貢獻者之心血結晶，在自由軟體產業裡的"
"經濟利潤或許比不上著作權專有軟體，但是這絕對不表示此等獲利可以被忽略，這樣的"
"結果就是致使普通的軟體使用者在絕大部分的情況下，可以不花費任何分文地盡情使用"
"自由軟體。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:37
msgid ""
"Free software is not about killing incentives for programmers. It's about "
"seeing code as knowledge which should not be hidden from the user. It works "
"with a different business model, in which many companies already do well."
msgstr ""
"自由軟體的宗旨並非在扼殺軟體開發者貢獻的誘因，而是在於將程式碼視為一種知識，"
"不應該被隱藏與封鎖於使用者之外。此種架構可以在多種不同的商業模式中予以應用，"
"實際上已經有許多公司企業在此等模式的經營下蓬勃發展。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:40
msgid "2. Innovation is killed in free software."
msgstr "2. 自由軟體扼殺創新。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:42
msgid ""
"The common perception is that if everyone can copy ideas, innovation will be "
"stifled."
msgstr ""
"很多普遍的觀點都認為，如果任何人都可以任意複製他人的創作，創新將會被封殺。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:43
msgid ""
"In fact, freedom is often <strong>the key to innovative and successful "
"software</strong>."
msgstr "但事實上，自由通常都是<strong>通往創新與成功軟體的關鍵</strong>。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:45
msgid "Anyone is allowed and encouraged to work upon it;"
msgstr "任何人都可以甚至歡迎參與它的創作；"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:46
msgid "Many people are willing to participate;"
msgstr "有許多人都很樂意去參與其中；"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:47
msgid ""
"There is no need to re-invent everything, ideas can be improved upon "
"directly."
msgstr ""
"完全沒有必要去重複發明已經存在的東西，而是能夠以創意去直接改良這些已經存在的"
"東西。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:50
msgid ""
"Non-proprietary software stands out in many areas: consider, to name just a "
"few:"
msgstr ""
"目前非著作權私有的軟體在許多方面已經有許多傑出的代表，底下就簡單列舉幾個："

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:52
msgid ""
"Applications: <a href=\"http://www.getfirefox.com/\">Firefox</a> (web "
"browser), <a href=\"http://www.inkscape.org/\">Inkscape</a> (vector drawing)."
msgstr ""
"應用軟體：<a href=\"http://www.getfirefox.com/\">Firefox 火狐</a> (網頁瀏覽"
"器)、<a href=\"http://www.inkscape.org/\">Inkscape</a>(向量繪圖軟體)。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:53
msgid ""
"Complete systems: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_HTTP_Server"
"\">Apache</a> (web server), <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenBSD"
"\">OpenBSD</a> (<abbr title=\"Operating System\">OS</abbr>), and of course, "
"GNU/Linux."
msgstr ""
"成套軟體系統：<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_HTTP_Server"
"\">Apache</a> (網頁伺服器)、<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenBSD"
"\">OpenBSD</a> (<abbr title=\"Operating System\">作業系統</abbr>)、以及顯而易"
"見的 GNU/Linux。"

#. translators: use URL to localized Wikipedia article for ODF, instead of opendocumentfellowship
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:56
msgid ""
"Formats and protocols: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML\">HTML</"
"a> (web pages), <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"BitTorrent_(protocol)\">BitTorrent</a> (file sharing), <a href=\"http://"
"opendocumentfellowship.com/\">ODF</a> (office documents)."
msgstr ""
"檔案格式以及通訊協定：<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML\">超文件標"
"記語言 (HTML)</a>、<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"BitTorrent_(protocol)\">BitTorrent</a> (點對點檔案傳輸)、<a href=\"http://zh."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%BC%80%E6%94%BE%E6%96%87%E6%A1%A3%E6%A0%BC%E5%BC%8F\">"
"開放式文件格式 (ODF)</a>。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:57
msgid ""
"Server applications: <a href=\"http://drupal.org/\">Drupal</a> (Content "
"Management System), <a href=\"http://www.wordpress.org/\">Wordpress</a> "
"(blog)."
msgstr ""
"伺服器端應用：<a href=\"http://drupal.org/\">Drupal</a> (內容管理系統)、<a "
"href=\"http://www.wordpress.org/\">Wordpress</a> (部落格系統)。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:62
msgid "3. Software Should Just Work (who cares about source code?)"
msgstr "3. 軟體只要能用就好了（誰會在意有沒有來源程式碼啊？）"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:64
msgid "Anyone should care about whether their software is free."
msgstr "任何人都應該關心他們所用的軟體是否自由。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:65
msgid ""
"Imagine purchasing a car whose hood you are forbidden to open. It does not "
"matter whether you know how a car works &ndash; the point is that nobody "
"will be able to check the engine. How can you trust your car, if no one is "
"allowed to make sure that it's reliable, that it does not leak, that it's "
"not harmful to the society and environment?"
msgstr ""
"試著假想一下如果你買了一輛車，但是廠商卻禁止你掀起引擎蓋，估且不論你是否了解"
"車輛的機械原理 &ndash; 重點是在於如此一來沒有人可以檢查你車上的引擎，如果沒有"
"人能夠去檢查確認它的情況是否正常，你如何能相信這輛車沒有漏油、安全性疑慮？也"
"不會對環境與社會造成危害？"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:66
msgid ""
"The idea is the same with software &ndash; except that code does "
"<strong>much more</strong> than move cars. Software runs our computers, "
"phones, TVs, media players and more, carrying information and our culture."
msgstr ""
"這對於軟體來說是同樣的道理 &ndash; 差別在於軟體的程式碼所做的事，並不只是單純"
"地推動車輛行駛而已。軟體運行在我們的電腦、手機、電視、多媒體播放機以及更多東"
"西，承載著資訊和我們的文化。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:67
msgid ""
"Free software is as important as free speech, as a free market. If software "
"is free, users have control and liberty over it."
msgstr ""
"軟體的自由和言論的自由是同等重要的，就像是自由市場一般，如果軟體是自由的，其"
"使用者就可以對其控制並且善加利用。"

#. translators: The %s placeholder will automatically point to the 'try and install' page
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:70
#, php-format
msgid ""
"The good news are: <em>free software also Just Works.</em> And in fact, it "
"often Just Works Better. <a href=\"%s\">Pop in a GNU/Linux liveCD</a> in "
"your computer at start-up, to try a full-featured, well-organised system, "
"without installation, so you can judge by yourself."
msgstr ""
"有個好消息是：<em>自由軟體是可以正常被使用的</em>，而且還更為好用。在你電腦開"
"機之際<a href=\"%s\">放進一片 GNU/Linux Live CD 光碟片</a>，就可以在不用進行"
"任何安裝程序的情況下，盡情地體驗這個功能完整且強大的作業系統，之後你便可自行"
"評估是否要正式地使用它。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:73
msgid ""
"4. Free software doesn't respect authors' copyrighted and patented software."
msgstr "4. 自由軟體不尊重軟體開發者受著作權與專利保護的軟體。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:75
msgid ""
"To answer this correctly, we must first make a clear distinction between "
"copyright and patents. Copyright is a right granted to the author over his/"
"her creation (for example, the text of a book, or the source code of a "
"program). A patent, on the other hand, is a purchased, registered exclusive "
"control over a process, the application of an idea."
msgstr ""
"為了正確地回答這個問題，我們首先必須釐清著作權和專利的不同點。著作權是賦予作"
"者所創造出來的作品的一種權利（例如：一本書裡的文字、或是一個程式裡的來源程式"
"碼）。另一方面，專利則是買斷並註冊的對於實現某種想法的過程的獨家控制權。"

#. translators: If you can, please use a non-official translation of the GPL, as found at http://www.gnu.org/licenses/translations.html
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:79
msgid ""
"<strong>Copyright is very important in free software.</strong> It is the "
"very mechanism, central to the <a href=\"http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html"
"\">GNU General Public License</a>, which ensures that free software remains "
"free, and that authors are credited for their work. Programs are "
"copyrighted, whether they are free or proprietary."
msgstr ""
"<strong>著作權對自由軟體來說是非常重要的。</strong>它就是<a href=\"http://"
"www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html\">GNU 通用公共授權條款</a>，它確保了自由軟體可"
"以保持自由，而且作者的努力可以得到肯定。無論是自由軟體或是專有軟體都受到著作"
"權保護。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:80
msgid ""
"Any proprietary software author can easily check that his copyright is not "
"violated in a free software application, since its source code is readily "
"available."
msgstr ""
"任何專有軟體的作者都可以輕鬆檢查自由軟體是否侵犯了他的著作權，因為自由軟體的"
"來源程式碼容易取得。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:82
msgid ""
"Patents in software, on the other hand, are a very controversial concept. To "
"put it shortly: there is <strong>no such thing as a \"patented software\"</"
"strong>. By registering for a patent, however, someone can claim ownership "
"over a <em>process</em>. The patent then applies to all software that use "
"this process, whether proprietary or free."
msgstr ""
"另一方面，軟體專利卻是一個相當具有爭議性的概念。簡而言之：<strong>根本就沒有"
"什麼「專利軟體」</strong>。然而，透過申請專利，某些人就可以聲稱對一項 <em>處"
"理過程</em> 的所有權。而不論是專有軟體或是自由軟體，只要是使用到這一個過程"
"的，都受其約束。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:83
msgid "Software patents:"
msgstr "軟體專利："

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:85
msgid "Are expensive and are granted only several years after application;"
msgstr "非常昂貴並且只在申請後的幾年內被承認；"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:86
msgid ""
"Are limited geographically (a patent granted in the US is worthless in "
"Europe);"
msgstr "受到地理性的限制 (一個在美國申請的專利在歐洲是無效的)；"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:87
msgid "Have long life-times (often 20 years) in a quickly-moving industry;"
msgstr "在一個快速變化的產業裡有很長的生命週期 (通常是20年)；"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:88
msgid ""
"Often apply <a href=\"http://eupat.ffii.org/patents/samples/\">entirely "
"trivial processes</a>."
msgstr ""
"往往被用在<a href=\"http://eupat.ffii.org/patents/samples/\">相當瑣碎的過程</"
"a>。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:90
msgid ""
"As such, they are seldom used to benefit innovators (and in fact, rarely "
"used by the innovators themselves)."
msgstr "因此，它們很難對創新者有利 (事實上，創新者們自己都鮮少使用專利)。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:92
msgid ""
"It's safe to say that <strong>any medium-size piece of software violates "
"patents</strong>, in several countries, whether it's free or not."
msgstr ""
"可以說在很多國家，不論是自由軟體或是專有軟體，<strong>有不少的軟體都侵犯了其"
"他軟體的專利</strong>。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:93
msgid ""
"Depending on the holding company's ability to cover very large legal costs, "
"or to retaliate with other patent threats, royalties and restrictions can be "
"applied over these patents."
msgstr ""
"視專利持有公司承擔巨額法律費用，或回擊其他專利威脅的能力而定，可對這些專利徵"
"收專利權使用費，制訂相關的限制措施。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:96
msgid "Read and view more:"
msgstr "閱讀並瞭解更多："

#. translators: Unless you know of a good localized resource, please leave the URL as such.
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:100
msgid ""
"<a href=\"http://ffii.org/Frequently_Asked_Questions_about_software_patents"
"\" hreflang=\"en\">Frequently Asked Questions on software patents, by the "
"<abbr title=\"Foundation for a Free Information Infrastructure\">FFII</abbr>"
msgstr ""
"<a href=\"http://ffii.org/Frequently_Asked_Questions_about_software_patents"
"\" hreflang=\"en\">軟體專利的常見問題，由<abbr title=\"Foundation for a Free "
"Information Infrastructure\">FFII</abbr>製作"

#. translators: Unless you know of a good localized resource, please leave the URL as such.
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:103
msgid ""
"<a href=\"http://www.redhat.com/magazine/007may05/features/ip/\" hreflang="
"\"en\">Short and clear video on \"intellectual property\" by Red Hat"
msgstr ""
"<a href=\"http://www.redhat.com/magazine/007may05/features/ip/\" hreflang="
"\"en\">Red Hat 公司出版的「知識產權」的簡短介紹影片"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:108
msgid "5. Free software is like communism."
msgstr "5. 自由軟體就像共產主義。"

#. translators: Here, the %s placeholder simply puts a link to a footnote in this page
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:112
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Supporters of this idea argue that there can be no private ownership with "
"free (or \"open source\" %s) software. Let's answer this with an example."
msgstr ""
"支持這個論點的人認為把軟體以自由 (或「開源」%s) 授權釋出將失去對該軟體的私人"
"財產權，我們將舉以下例子說明："

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:113
msgid ""
"Let's imagine that you use one application that is free software, at home "
"and within your company. You find a great way to improve it, so now with "
"your modified version, your computer works better and your factories run "
"twice as fast!"
msgstr ""
"想像一下，你正在同時在家裡以及你的公司使用一個自由軟體，你發現一個改進它的好"
"方法，而這個你自行改進的版本的電腦運作得更好且工廠產生兩倍的效益！"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:114
msgid ""
"This modified version is <strong>your own version</strong>. You are not "
"required to tell anyone about it, nor must you share any of the profits you "
"made using it. You are simply exerting your freedom to use and modify free "
"software."
msgstr ""
"這個修改的版本是<strong>你自己的版本</strong>，你並沒有義務要通知任何人，或必"
"須分享你的以此軟體的營利，只是單純的善用使用與修改自由軟體的自由權。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:115
msgid ""
"What the free software license requires is that <strong>if you redistribute</"
"strong> this software, then you must keep it free. Namely, if you sell CDs "
"with your software on them, or start letting people outside your home or "
"company use it, then you must:"
msgstr ""
"而自由軟體授權要求 <strong>假如你重新散布</strong> 這個軟體，它必須維持自由，"
"換句話說，假如你販售內含你的軟體的 CD，或者讓你家中或公司以外的人使用它，你必"
"須："

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:117
msgid ""
"Either give everyone the same rights you had when you obtained the original "
"software, that is, the freedom to inspect, modify and redistribute your "
"modified version;"
msgstr ""
"授權任何人你從源始軟體取得的授權，也就是說，探查、修改、再散布你修改的版本的"
"自由；"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:118
msgid ""
"Or, make the original software and your secret addition to it clearly "
"separate (that is, your addition should contain none of the original work)."
msgstr ""
"或者，清楚的劃分源始軟體以及你的獨門配方 (也就是說，你的修正並不包含任何原本"
"的作品)。"

#. translators: The %s placeholder here will automatically point to the page "Windows Restrictions, further details"
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:122
#, php-format
msgid ""
"So in fact, you have more \"ownership\" over free software than over "
"proprietary software &ndash;where the programmer decides everything you can "
"<a href=\"%s\">and can't do</a> with the software."
msgstr ""
"所以，實際上，你在自由軟體的「所有權」上比專有軟體更多 &ndash; 後者由軟體工程"
"師決定你<a href=\"%s\">能與不能</a>讓軟體做什麼。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:123
msgid ""
"<em>Free software has nothing to do with a political system.</em> You can "
"run free software on top of proprietary software, just as well as the "
"opposite. The free software license is simply a legal, ethical contract "
"between the programmer and the end-user."
msgstr ""
"<em>自由軟體與任何政治體系都無關。</em> 你可以在專有軟體之上使用自由軟體，反"
"之亦然。自由軟體授權單純的只是程式設計師以及一般使用者在法律上的、道德上的合"
"約。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:127
msgid "Read more:"
msgstr "深入瞭解："

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:130
msgid "Free / \"open-source\" software can't be secure."
msgstr "自由 /「開源」軟體可能不安全。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:133
msgid ""
"The argument generally goes that since the source code of free software is "
"available, it is less likely to be secure."
msgstr ""
"這個觀點一般都是說因為自由軟體的來源程式碼是可以公開檢視的，所以比較不可能會"
"安全。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:134
msgid ""
"Short answer: The majority of servers run free software. They are the major "
"networked computers holding sensitive or confidential information such as "
"your bank details or trade secrets."
msgstr ""
"一個簡潔有力的回答：絕大多數的伺服器執行的都是自由軟體。而它們可能是存有你的"
"帳戶資料、或是交易機密等敏感資料的連上網路的電腦。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:135
msgid ""
"A more precise answer is that availability of source code is a warrant of "
"security, not a weakness. The freedom of the software ensures it can be "
"inspected, tested and improved by a very wide community. A good lock is "
"secure because the technology used to design it is open, though only the key "
"holder can open it. The same goes for software."
msgstr ""
"一個更加確切的回答是，可以取得的來源程式碼是安全的保證，而不是隱憂。軟體的自"
"由確保了它可以被廣泛的社群查看、測試並且改進。一把好的鎖即使公佈了設計它的技"
"術仍然是安全的，因為仍然只有鑰匙的持有者才能打開它。而軟體也是如此。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:136
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Need examples? Have a look at the <a href=\"http://www.getfirefox.com/"
"\">Firefox browser</a>, the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Apache_HTTP_Server\">Apache HTTP Server</a>, the <a href=\"http://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Pretty_Good_Privacy\">OpenPGP</a> encryption system, or "
"the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenBSD\">OpenBSD</a> operating "
"system. And <a href=\"%s#security\">there are no spyware or viruses under "
"GNU/Linux</a>."
msgstr ""
"想要看些例子？看看 <a href=\"http://www.getfirefox.com/\">Firefox 瀏覽器</"
"a>，<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_HTTP_Server\">Apache HTTP "
"伺服器</a>，<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pretty_Good_Privacy"
"\">OpenPGP</a> 加密系統，或是 <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenBSD"
"\">OpenBSD</a> 作業系統。而且在 <a href=\"%s#security\">GNU/Linux 裡並沒有間"
"諜軟體或是病毒的存在</a>。"

#. translators: this can be translated loosely, ex "Free software isolates me" or else.
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:143
msgid "I'm on my own with free software."
msgstr "使用自由軟體只能靠自己。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:146
msgid "Not at all."
msgstr "完全不是。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:148
msgid ""
"If you are looking for good documentation and support forums to assist you, "
"there is plenty available for free (\"open source\") software."
msgstr ""
"如果你要尋求好的文件以及支援論壇來幫助你，那麼每個自由 (「開源」) 軟體幾乎都"
"有。"

#. translators: use your best knowledge of the community to propose localized links ;-)
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:150
msgid ""
"Each GNU/Linux distribution has its own community (for example, <a href="
"\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support/free\">Ubuntu support</a> or <a href="
"\"http://fedora.redhat.com/docs/\">Fedora docs</a>), but there are also "
"general free software help communities, like <a href=\"http://www."
"linuxquestions.org/\">LinuxQuestions.org</a>."
msgstr ""
"多數的 GNU/Linux 散佈版都會有自己的社群 (例如<a href=\"http://www.ubuntu-tw."
"org/\">Ubuntu 正體中文站</a>或是<a href=\"https://fedora-tw.org/\">Fedora 中"
"文論壇</a>)，不過也有通用的幫助社群，例如<a href=\"http://www.linuxquestions."
"org/\">LinuxQuestions.org</a>。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:151
msgid ""
"If you need someone you can reach on the phone anytime to assist you, the "
"companies behind most distributions provide commercial support: see the <a "
"href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support/paid\">Ubuntu Commercial Support</a> or "
"<a href=\"http://www.redhat.com/rhel/\">Red Hat Enterprise Linux</a> pages "
"for example."
msgstr ""
"如果你需要的是有人可以在電話的另一端幫助你，那麼有些散佈版背後會有公司提供商"
"業支援：例如<a href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/support/paid\">Ubuntu 商業支援</"
"a> 或是 <a href=\"http://www.redhat.com/rhel/\">Red Hat 企業版 Linux</a>等。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:157
msgid "Further reading on the web"
msgstr "在網路上了解更多"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:161
msgid ""
"This is where free software all started. You will find a wealth of "
"information about the free software philosophy, the history of the project, "
"and the stands taken by the <a href=\"http://www.fsf.org/\">Free Software "
"Foundation</a> (the organisation behind GNU)."
msgstr ""
"這可以說是自由軟體的濫觴，你能從這裡獲得大量關於自由軟體哲學的資訊、這個計畫"
"的歷史，以及 <a href=\"http://www.fsf.org/\">自由軟體基金會 (FSF)</a> (GNU 背"
"後的組織) 跨出的每一步足跡。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:164
msgid ""
"The concept of Free&nbsp;/&nbsp;Libre&nbsp;/&nbsp;Open Source Software "
"presented in a highly readable, friendly way. A must-read."
msgstr "簡單明瞭的自由&nbsp;/&nbsp;開源軟體的概念，新手必讀。"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:167
msgid ""
"A simple and clear website about the free format OpenDocument, showing the "
"importance of freedom in formats (not just in applications)."
msgstr ""
"關於 OpenDocument 自由格式，彰顯格式自由化的重要性的，簡單清楚的網頁。(並非只"
"是應用程式)"

#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:170
msgid ""
"An engaged article by co-founder of <a href=\"http://www.wikipedia.org/"
"\">Wikipedia</a> Jimmy Wales, which shows the connections between freedom in "
"software and free knowledge."
msgstr ""
"由 <a href=\"http://www.wikipedia.org/\">維基百科</a>的共同創辦人 Jimmy "
"Wales 撰寫凸顯軟體自由性以及知識自由的關聯的文章。"

#. translators: This is the content of the footnote, at the bottom of the page
#: lib/views/linux.misunderstanding_free_software.php:179
#, php-format
msgid ""
"What we call \"Free Software\" here is also often called \"Open Source "
"Software\". In practice the requirements are identical, although because the "
"term \"open\" doesn't call to mind freedom, it <a href=\"http://www.gnu.org/"
"philosophy/open-source-misses-the-point.html\">misses the point</a>. Read "
"our FAQ entry: <a href=\"%s#open_source\">Are \"Open Source\" and \"Free "
"Software\" the same thing?</a>."
msgstr ""
"我們所指的「自由軟體」也常被稱為「開源軟體」。實務上兩者的需求十分相近，雖然"
"「開源」並不暗示自由，「開源」<a href=\"http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/open-"
"source-misses-the-point.html\">忽略的東西</a>。閱讀我們的 FAQ：<a href="
"\"%s#open_source\">「開源軟體」與「自由軟體」相同的東西嗎？</a>。"

#. translators: please note the "affirmative" tone with the '.' at end of sentence.
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.php:27
msgid "Meet GNU/Linux in everyday use."
msgstr "看看日常生活中的 GNU/Linux 使用狀況。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.php:41
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:182
msgid "Our selection for an easy choice."
msgstr "我們以簡單易用為原則的精選。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.php:55
msgid "Install it! (it's easier than you think)"
msgstr "安裝它吧！( 這比想像中的簡單 )"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:23
msgid ""
"Make the step &ndash; unless you wish to <a href=\"http://linuxpreloaded.com/"
"\" title=\"Linux Desktops and Laptops\">purchase a PC with Linux pre-"
"installed</a>, you can see what freedom looks like on your computer."
msgstr ""
"按照下面的步驟 &ndash; 除非你希望<a href=\"http://linuxpreloaded.com/\" "
"title=\"Linux Desktops and Laptops\">購買一臺預裝 Linux 的電腦</a>，你將會在"
"你的電腦上體會到自由的可貴。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:30
msgid "Try out: the live CD"
msgstr "試用：Live CD"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:32
msgid "Take no risk"
msgstr "不須承擔風險"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:36
msgid ""
"Using a live CD means that Linux will be running on your computer "
"<em>without installing anything</em>. It's a risk-less way to try and see by "
"yourself what Linux is."
msgstr ""
"使用 Live CD 表示 Linux 會在<em>不安裝任何軟體</em>的情況下在你的電腦上執行。"
"這是讓你親自試用並就近觀察 Linux 而風險最低的方法。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:37
msgid ""
"When running on a live CD, your computer uses solely the CD-ROM to work "
"(without accessing the hard drive inside). You can launch all of the default "
"programs, edit documents, and browse the web."
msgstr ""
"在 Live CD 模式時，電腦只會單純的使用光碟機運作 ( 並不會進入內接硬碟 ) 。你可"
"以執行所有預裝的程式，編輯文件，以及瀏覽網路。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:38
msgid ""
"Since it is only designed as a trial mode, it is a little slow (it will take "
"you five minutes to boot up, and programs launch somewhat slowly). If you "
"proceed to install, the system will go much faster."
msgstr ""
"因為這被設計為試用模式，所以可能會有點慢 (視情況而定，你可能需要幾分鐘來啟動"
"你的系統，而程式啟動可能會有點緩慢)。如果安裝在你的電腦上，運行速度將會快非常"
"多。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:40
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:54
msgid "What you need"
msgstr "你需要什麼"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:42
msgid ""
"To use a live CD, you need a little bit of curiosity and fifteen minutes of "
"free time, but <strong>no advanced knowledge in computing</strong>. If you "
"feel confident simply using Windows from time to time, then this is within "
"your reach."
msgstr ""
"要使用 Live CD ，你需意一點好奇心以及幾十分鐘的時間，不需要<strong>具備進階的"
"電腦知識</strong>。如果你在日常生活中會操作 Windows，那麼這個對你也不成問題。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:48
msgid "Installing as a dual boot"
msgstr "以多重開機模式安裝"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:50
msgid "Choose at start-up"
msgstr "選擇一個開機模式"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:51
msgid ""
"It is possible to install GNU/Linux along with Windows. This means that upon "
"start-up, you will be greeted with a screen allowing you to boot into the "
"operating system you prefer."
msgstr ""
"將 GNU/Linux 跟 Windows 安裝在一起是可行的，也就是說，在開機時，你將會在螢幕"
"上看到選擇你想開機的作業系統選單。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:52
msgid ""
"Setting up a dual-boot can be helpful if you need time to abandon "
"restrictive software. It is <a href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/"
"install-desktop-latest\" title=\"a tutorial on installing Ubuntu\">not "
"difficult to set-up</a>, though erasing Windows altogether is even easier."
msgstr ""
"如果放棄受限制的軟體需要時間，你可以選擇安裝雙系統， <a href=\"http://www."
"ubuntu.com/download/desktop/install-desktop-latest\" title=\"Ubuntu安裝指南"
"\">而這並不困難</a>，雖然將 Windows 徹底刪除會更加簡單。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:55
msgid ""
"Installing Linux on your computer will take you less than 30 minutes. It is "
"not an obvious step for complete beginners, but if you use computers on a "
"daily basis this is very likely within your reach. If you have already re-"
"installed Windows on your computer, rest assured that installing Linux is no "
"harder."
msgstr ""
"在你的電腦上安裝 Linux 只需要小於 30 分鐘，這對完全新手而言並不是很淺顯的步"
"驟，但假如你經常使用電腦的話應該不難。尤其是在電腦上重灌過 Windows ，那安裝 "
"Linux 的步驟並不會比較難。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:61
msgid "Get the CD or DVD you need"
msgstr "取得需要的 CD 或 DVD"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:63
msgid ""
"For the distributions we recommend, the live CD/DVD is the same as the "
"installation CD/DVD. You can either download and burn a CD/DVD yourself, or "
"order a CD/DVD from a trusted vendor."
msgstr ""
"對於我們推薦的這些散佈版而言，Live CD/DVD 和安裝時使用的 CD/DVD 是相同的。你"
"可以自己下載並燒錄一張，或者從你信任的發行商手中取得這些 CD/DVD。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:68
msgid ""
"You can download an <code>iso</code> image (rather large file) and then <a "
"href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/burn-a-dvd-on-windows\">burn "
"it to a CD or DVD</a>. Once the CD/DVD is burned, you can use it to <a href="
"\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/install-desktop-latest\">install "
"Ubuntu</a> onto your computer."
msgstr ""
"你可以下載 <code>ISO</code> 映像檔（一個蠻大的檔案）然後<a href=\"http://www."
"ubuntu.com/download/desktop/burn-a-dvd-on-windows\">將其燒錄為一張 CD 或者 "
"DVD</a>。之後你便可以用它 <a href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop/"
"install-desktop-latest\">將 Ubuntu 安裝進你的電腦</a>。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:72
msgid "Download Ubuntu"
msgstr "下載 Ubuntu"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:75
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:91
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:107
msgid "Order a CD/DVD"
msgstr "訂購 CD/DVD"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:84
msgid ""
"The Fedora live CD/DVD also enables installation. Follow the <a href="
"\"http://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-US/Fedora/18/html/"
"Installation_Quick_Start_Guide/index.html\">installation quick start guide</"
"a> to get started with Fedora."
msgstr ""
"Fedora 的 Live CD/DVD 同時也可以用於安裝。你可以根據 <a href=\"http://docs."
"fedoraproject.org/en-US/Fedora/18/html/Installation_Quick_Start_Guide/index."
"html\">快速安裝指南</a> 開始使用 Fedora。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:88
msgid "Download Fedora"
msgstr "下載 Fedora"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:100
msgid ""
"The <a href=\"http://trisquel.info/en/wiki/installation-guide\">Trisquel "
"installation</a> is very similar to that of Ubuntu."
msgstr ""
"<a href=\"http://trisquel.info/en/wiki/installation-guide\">Trisquel 的安裝</"
"a>與 Ubuntu 非常相似。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:104
msgid "Download Trisquel"
msgstr "下載 Trisquel"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:113
msgid ""
"Note: Purchased and downloaded CDs are identical! GNU/Linux is <a href="
"\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"What do you mean, free?\">free "
"software</a>. You are simply paying a handling/shipping fee."
msgstr ""
"注意：購買或者下載的 CD 是相同的！GNU/Linux 是<a href=\"http://www."
"softwareliberty.com/\" title=\"What do you mean, free?\">自由軟體</a>。你僅僅"
"負擔了手續/運費而已。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:120
msgid "Free Software pre-installed"
msgstr "預裝自由軟體"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.try_or_install.php:122
msgid ""
"Not all computers are shipped with Windows. If you do not wish to make the "
"install yourself, or are in need of new hardware, you can get a laptop or a "
"desktop pre-installed with GNU/Linux.<br/>\n"
"We have compiled <a title=\"linux computers\" href=\"http://linuxpreloaded."
"com/\">a list of vendors pre-installing Linux at LinuxPreloaded.com</a> just "
"for that reason."
msgstr ""
"並不是所有的電腦都是預裝 Windows 的。如果你不想要自己動手安裝，或是需要新的硬"
"體，你可以選擇購買預裝GNU/Linux 的筆記型電腦或是桌上型電腦。<br/>\n"
"我們為你列出了<a title=\"linux computers\" href=\"http://linuxpreloaded.com/"
"\">一個販賣預裝 Linux 作業系統的電腦廠商列表</a>。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:23
msgid "Stand for a Free Society"
msgstr "為了自由的社會"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:26
msgid ""
"There is much more to software than being trustworthy (being \"Open-Source"
"\"): what really counts is <strong>the freedoms you get</strong> over it. "
"Can you learn from it? Can you build upon it? Can you distribute it? That's "
"what we refer to as \"free software\"."
msgstr ""
"軟體的價值比起是否值得信任 (例如「開放源始碼」) 更重要：真正的重點的是"
"<strong>你能透過它所獲得的自由</strong>。你是否能從中學習？你是否能在它上面繼"
"續構建？你是否能繼續散佈它？這些價值就是我們所說的「自由軟體」。"

#. translators: This is the quote by Don Marti at the start of the article.
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:32
msgid ""
"I come up with new words, phrases, analogies, all kinds of fun stuff in the "
"English language and people paraphrase what I had to say and make money "
"talking about some of the same things that I did."
msgstr ""
"我想到了新的詞語、成語、比喻、還有各種英語中的趣味，而人們改述我說過的話，並"
"且透過談論那些我曾說過的話來賺錢。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:33
msgid ""
"<strong>If I try to lock down</strong> what I talk about and write about, "
"the same way as a proprietary software company does, then the whole industry "
"of speaking, writing, media, would be overly litigious, and transaction "
"costs would be prohibitive."
msgstr ""
"<strong>如果我試著把我所說過的話和所寫的字封鎖起來</strong>，就像是專有軟體公"
"司所做的一樣，那麼所有演說、寫作、媒體相關的產業都將很容易被告上法院，還有和"
"解的費用都會高昂地令人望而卻步。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:37
msgid "Not a crazy concept"
msgstr "並非是瘋狂的理念"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:39
msgid ""
"It sounds peculiar to many users that software should be free as in freedom, "
"since none of Microsoft's products are. Yet our society works with many free "
"things in it, for example:"
msgstr ""
"這對於許多使用者來說聽起來可能很奇特，因為微軟的任何一個產品都不曾給予過使用"
"者這種自由。我們的社會正在為這種自由而努力著，例如："

#. translators: This is the short quote on the side of the article.
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:44
msgid ""
"Though no one has a proprietary lock on yoga, it is still a thriving $30 "
"billion business in the United States."
msgstr ""
"因為沒有人擁有對瑜珈的所有權，因此它在美國至今擁有超過300億美元產值的興旺產"
"業。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:49
msgid ""
"No chef would ever forbid you to modify his recipe and make derivatives out "
"of it. The food industry thrives despite being required by law to list "
"ingredients on product labels."
msgstr ""
"沒有廚師會禁止你修改他的食譜，然後從其變化出更棒的佳餚。食品產業依規定只必須"
"將成份列在標籤上，但依舊可以蓬勃發展。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:50
msgid ""
"A fair law court system permits anyone to read through all the trial "
"hearings and arguments. Not only the result (the final deliberations), but "
"also the process is fully open."
msgstr ""
"一個公平的司法體系允許任何人閱讀所有的聽審以及證據。不僅只是結果(最終的審判結"
"果) 而已，還要這整個過程完全公開。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:53
msgid ""
"Free software is free as in &quot;free speech&quot;, as in a &quot;free "
"market&quot;: all are necessary for a free society. Unconvinced? Let us look "
"at proprietary software a little closer."
msgstr ""
"自由軟體並不僅僅在「言論」上是自由的，在「市場」上也是自由的：這些在自由的社"
"會中都是必要的。不服氣？讓我們再來仔細瞧瞧專有軟體吧。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:55
msgid "Proprietary software going wrong"
msgstr "專有軟體走向錯誤的道路"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:57
#, php-format
msgid ""
"The limits of proprietary software go beyond the security issue (see <a href="
"\"%s\">our article on source code</a>): today proprietary software "
"interferes with the spread of culture and information. This happens mainly "
"through two technologies:"
msgstr ""
"專有軟體的限制不只是安全問題（請見<a href=\"%s\">我們有關來源程式碼的文章</"
"a>）：今天專有軟體對文化與資訊傳播的干涉，主要是採取了以下兩種技術："

#. translators: This is sometimes only known as "DRM" in some languages. Please choose the vocabulary carefully. The %s placeholder links to a footnote which explains why we use the term "Digital Restrictions Management": http://www.getgnulinux.org/windows/stand_for_a_free_society/#footnote_bottom1
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:62
#, php-format
msgid "Digital Restrictions Management %s (DRM)"
msgstr "數位限制管理 %s (DRM)"

#. translators: The %s placeholder will automatically point to the footnote on bottom of page
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:66
#, php-format
msgid ""
"The main idea of DRM %s is to restrict access to files. Users encounter this "
"when, for example, they purchase music through iTunes, and then can only "
"play their music with one player, from one brand. With this method, "
"companies fight copyright infringement, but they also severely restrain "
"users' access to their files."
msgstr ""
"DRM %s 的主要想法是限制檔案的存取權。例如，如果使用者在 iTunes 上面購買了音"
"樂，那麼他們就只能在自己的播放器上面播放這些音樂，透過這些手段，音樂公司成功"
"的打擊著作權侵害，但同時也嚴重地限制了使用者要如何運用這些檔案。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:70
msgid "DRM is control over content"
msgstr "DRM 控制了內容"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:73
msgid ""
"Except that the control is not in the hands of the end-user. The original "
"purpose of <abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions Management\">DRM</abbr> is "
"understandable, but the implications over the flow of information and "
"culture within a society are frightening."
msgstr ""
"只是控制的權利並非掌握在終端用戶手中。<abbr title=\"數位限制管理, Digital "
"Restrictions Management\">DRM</abbr> 的本意相當清楚，但是對於社會中資訊和文化"
"的流動所造成的影響卻令人感到畏懼。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:77
msgid ""
"Imagine a book that automatically became glued shut after you read it once."
msgstr "想像一本書在閱讀完以後會自動黏死。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:78
msgid ""
"Imagine documents that self-destructed if you tried to take them out of the "
"room."
msgstr "想像一下試圖帶出房間就會自動銷毀的文件。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:79
msgid ""
"Imagine telephones that only worked if the person you were ringing was "
"renting the same make and model."
msgstr "想像必須要對方跟你租借同樣製造商以及型號時才會接通的電話。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:83
msgid "Sounds crazy? This is where Trusted Computing comes in."
msgstr "聽起來很瘋狂嗎？這就是信任式運算的由來。"

#. translators: This is sometimes only known as "Trusted Computing", not TC, in some languages. Please choose the vocabulary carefully.
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:87
msgid "Trusted Computing (TC)"
msgstr "信任式運算 (TC)"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:89
msgid ""
"Trusted Computing (sometimes <a href=\"http://www.lafkon.net/tc/\" title=\"A "
"very well done video on Trusted Computing\">more accurately</a> called "
"\"Treacherous Computing\") means a computer can only run \"Trusted\" "
"Software. It is meant to be an uncircumventable protection against nuisances "
"(like viruses or spyware) and copyright violations (people copying "
"proprietary software)."
msgstr ""
"信任式運算 (Trusted Computing) (有時候 <a href=\"http://www.lafkon.net/tc/\" "
"title=\"關於信任式運算的很好的影片\">更準確地</a> 稱之為「取巧式運算 "
"(Treacherous Computing)」) 代表一臺電腦只能執行「可信任的」軟體。其目的是為了"
"防止滋擾 (如病毒或間諜軟體) 或是著作權侵犯 (例如人們複製專有軟體)。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:92
msgid "Trusted Computing is control over the computer"
msgstr "信任式運算控制了電腦"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:95
msgid ""
"The critical thing about Trusted Computing is that <strong>you cannot "
"decide</strong> what is trustworthy and what is not. For example, your "
"computer might refuse to run programs that are not certified by the software "
"company &ndash;programs that could enable you to take documents out of the "
"office, or play your neighbour's DVD, or send your essay to someone not "
"using the same program."
msgstr ""
"信任式運算所帶來的最嚴重的問題是，<strong>你無法決定</strong>哪些是可信任的而"
"哪些不是。例如，您的電腦可能會拒絕執行那些不被軟體公司所認可的軟體 &ndash; 這"
"可能是允許您把文件帶出您的辦公室，或是播放您鄰居的 DVD，或是將您的文章寄給一"
"個並非使用相同程式的人之類的軟體。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:96
msgid ""
"A whole range of possibilities opens up for companies that benefit from "
"restricting your computing (such as proprietary software and recording "
"companies). It is suddenly possible to rent DVDs that only play two times, "
"or music you can only listen to during September, or information you can "
"read but can't save or copy. All of a sudden, Trusted Computing and DRM "
"enable <strong>remote control</strong> over content."
msgstr ""
"這所有因而開啟的可能性使得各公司 (專有軟體公司或是音樂公司) 可以透過限制你的"
"電腦該如何使用而獲益。或許有一天，租到一張只能播放兩次的 DVD，或是只能在 9月"
"份才可以聽的音樂，又或是只能供你閱讀但不能儲存或複製的資訊，都可能在轉瞬間成"
"為現實。突然之間，信任式運算以及 DRM 開啟 <strong>遠端控制</strong> 住內容的"
"可能性。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:97
msgid ""
"Trusted Computing, in effect, enables the publisher to write their own "
"copyright law."
msgstr ""
"信任式運算，就實際影響來說，就是讓發行單位去編寫屬於他們自己的著作權法。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:100
msgid "The wider impact"
msgstr "更廣泛的影響"

#. translators: This is the quote by Rosemary Bechler in the middle of the article.
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:105
msgid ""
"Many cultural products are now emerging &quot;triple protected&quot;, not "
"only by copyright and code, but also by contracts or licenses for which "
"users waive all remaining rights."
msgstr ""
"許多文化產品現在都有了「三重保護」不只是著作權和法律，還有許多的契約及授權條"
"款來讓使用者放棄所剩無幾的權利。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:106
msgid ""
"Increasingly, copyright is replaced with click-through end-user licenses for "
"digital content, using contract law to establish the absolute property "
"rights that copyright laws were originally intended to deny to publishers."
msgstr ""
"越來越多的數位內容著作權被需要讓終端使用者點擊通過的終端使用者授權條款取代，"
"發行單位使用契約法建立了原本著作權法拒絕給予的絕對財產權。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:110
msgid ""
"Computing is not just about calculations anymore. We use software to "
"communicate: to share information, ideas and culture. Software is in our "
"phones, cars, media players, TVs, and gets to govern just about every new "
"device around us."
msgstr ""
"電腦已經不只是用來計算而已了。我們使用軟體溝通：包括分享資訊、想法、以及文"
"化。軟體在我們的電話、車子、媒體播放器、電視中隨處可見，並開始掌管我們身邊的"
"每項新設備。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:117
msgid ""
"<strong>Software is increasingly used to enforce rules</strong>. Rules that "
"may or may not be the law. Rules that may or may not be fair. If the "
"software is not free there will be no space for the user to influence these "
"rules."
msgstr ""
"<strong>軟體逐漸被用來強制執行規則</strong>。規則可以是，也可以不是法律。規則"
"可能公平也可能不公平。如果軟體不是自由的，那麼使用者永遠也不會有機會改變這些"
"規則。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:119
msgid ""
"Trusted Computing and DRM pave the way for a society in which culture and "
"information are not simply turned into products (they are right now, and "
"that is fine), but into <em>consumable</em> products."
msgstr ""
"想想未來，文化和資訊不再只是轉化成產品 (它們現在是，這沒有問題)，而成為了一種"
"<em>消耗性</em>產品。信任式運算和 DRM 正為這樣的社會鋪了一條新路。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:121
msgid ""
"Code is power. Most of today's work documents are written and encoded with "
"secret algorithms in proprietary software. What will be of tomorrow's books, "
"photos, films, essays, animations, music, news? Proprietary programs such as "
"Windows have no transparency. A free culture and a free society cannot grow "
"from such software."
msgstr ""
"源碼就是力量。今天許多的工作文件是在專有軟體中編寫完成的，它們被寫於、編碼於"
"秘密的演算法中。而明天的書本、攝影作品、電影、文章、動畫、音樂甚至新聞會是什"
"麼樣子？像 Windows 這樣的專有軟體沒有任何透明可言。一個自由的文化和自由的社會"
"無法受益於諸如此類的軟體而成長茁壯。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:123
#, php-format
msgid "May we suggest you <a href=\"%s\">switch to Linux</a>?"
msgstr "我們可以建議你 <a href=\"%s\">擁抱 Linux 嗎</a>？"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:128
msgid ""
"Note that DRM is often referred to as \"Digital Rights Management\", "
"although it has little to do with rights &ndash; \"Digital Restrictions "
"Management\" is a more accurate name."
msgstr ""
"注意：DRM 一般是「數位權利管理 (Digital Rights Management)」的簡稱。雖然它確"
"實有做一些關於著作權的事情，但「數位限制管理 (Digital Restrictions "
"Management)」會是更準確的稱呼。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:138
msgid ""
"What is the Trusted Computing world like? This is a short story by Richard "
"Stallman that describes how this can affect any of us."
msgstr ""
"信任式運算的世界看起來是什麼樣子？這是一篇由自由軟體之父理查·斯托曼 (Richard "
"Stallman) 所寫的短篇故事，闡述了信任式運算如何影響我們之中的任何一個人。"

#. translators: Unless you know of a very good resource about DRM, please point to the Wikipedia article about DRM in your language, if it exists
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:142
msgid "http://www.timj.co.uk/computing/politics-policy/drm/fallacy/"
msgstr "https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/DRM"

#. translators: Title of external link
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:144
msgid "The fallacy of DRM"
msgstr "DRM"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:145
msgid ""
"A very well constructed article about <abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions "
"Management\">DRM</abbr> by Tim Jackson, and on which we based the present "
"article."
msgstr ""
"一篇由 Tim Jackson 所寫，關於 <abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions Management"
"\">DRM</abbr> 的好文章，我們這篇文章就是根據它所寫成的。"

#. translators: If you don't know of a localized version of this article, please leave the URL in English
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:149
msgid ""
"http://jimmywales.com/2004/10/21/free-knowledge-requires-free-software-and-"
"free-file-formats/"
msgstr ""
"http://jimmywales.com/2004/10/21/free-knowledge-requires-free-software-and-"
"free-file-formats/"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:149
msgid "Free Knowledge requires Free Software and Free File Formats"
msgstr "自由的知識需要自由軟體和自由的檔案格式"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:150
msgid ""
"An engaged article by Jimmy Wales, who co-founded the free encyclopedia <a "
"href=\"http://www.wikipedia.org/\">Wikipedia</a>."
msgstr ""
"一篇由自由的<a href=\"http://www.wikipedia.org/\">維基</a>百科聯合創始人 "
"Jimmy Wales 所創作，引人入勝的文章。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:153
msgid "http://www.lafkon.net/tc/"
msgstr "http://www.lafkon.net/tc/"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:153
msgid "Trusted Computing"
msgstr "信任式運算"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:154
msgid ""
"Short video animation by Benjamin Stephan and Lutz Vogel. A clear, snappy "
"and convincing argument."
msgstr ""
"由 Benjamin Stephan 和 Lutz Vogel 創作的短片。一則清晰、活潑、令人信服的論"
"述。"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:156
msgid "Why Software Should Not Have Owners"
msgstr "為什麼軟體不應該被誰專有"

#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:157
msgid ""
"A pivotal text for the Free Software movement by Richard Stallman. It "
"clarifies common objections and explains a handful of important ideas."
msgstr ""
"一段理查·斯托曼 (Richard Stallman) 為自由軟體運動所寫的非常重要的文字。它闡述"
"了關於抵制的共識，並解釋了自由軟體運動的重要思想。"

#. translators: This describes the last link, which will automatically point to the 'Misunderstanding Free Software' article
#: lib/views/windows.stand_for_a_free_society.php:161
msgid "More on free software on this website."
msgstr "這個網站上更多關於自由軟體的內容。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:23
msgid ""
"This is what everyday users usually find better, mostly the same, or not as "
"good, when switching from Windows to Linux."
msgstr ""
"這是日常使用者從 Windows 轉換到 Linux 時認為比較好、大部分相仿、或者略差的地"
"方。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:32
msgid "What is better in Linux"
msgstr "Linux 有哪些長處"

#. translators: please note the punctuation should be consistent
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:37
msgid "It's free"
msgstr "它是自由的"

#. translators: link to Free Software definition on GNU.org site, if softwareliberty.com is not translated in your language
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:41
msgid ""
"Unlike Windows, GNU/Linux is <a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" "
"title=\"What does Free Software mean?\">free software</a> &ndash; free as in "
"freedom. Install it on all computers and make copies for your friends! You "
"can even study it, transform it as you please, or build and sell your own "
"distribution."
msgstr ""
"不像 Windows，GNU/Linux 是<a href=\"http://www.softwareliberty.com/\" title="
"\"What does Free Software mean?\">自由軟體</a> &ndash; free as in freedom。可"
"以安裝在所有電腦，拷貝分發給你的朋友！你甚至可以隨心所欲的研究它、改變它，或"
"者建構並販售你自己的散佈版。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:45
msgid "Programs"
msgstr "各種程式"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:47
msgid ""
"There are a wealth of free applications available at no cost under Linux. To "
"edit professional documents, burn music CDs, rework photos, design a "
"website, or organise music; there's no need for $200 software with "
"restrictive licenses."
msgstr ""
"Linux 下有豐富的自由軟體可供免費使用。無論是編輯文件、燒錄音樂光碟、修圖、設"
"計網頁，或者是管理音樂；沒必要花 4000、5000 塊臺幣來購買受限制的授權。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:48
msgid ""
"The internal installer makes it incredibly easy to find, install and remove "
"programs."
msgstr "內建的安裝管理員讓搜尋、安裝、移除程式變的非比尋常的簡單。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:49
msgid ""
"It's also safe: you can forget the demo/trial crippled software, or harmful "
"freeware polluting the web."
msgstr ""
"它也很安全：你可以忘卻那些展示/試用的閹割軟體，或者是汙染網路的有害免費軟體。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:53
msgid "No fighting"
msgstr "不再掙扎"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:55
msgid ""
"Keeping your computer in shape over time needn't be a struggle. One year on, "
"GNU/Linux runs just as fast as the first day. And it may bring your old PC "
"back to life."
msgstr ""
"不再掙扎著維持你的系統運作得像剛安裝的一樣，一年以後，GNU/Linux 依然像第一天"
"一樣的運作順暢，且它可能會對你的老電腦施展回春魔法。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:56
msgid ""
"Also, Linux lets you choose what you want and what you don't. If you had a "
"hard time getting rid of MSN Messenger, Windows Update notifications, or "
"Clippit the paperclip, you'll find it refreshing."
msgstr ""
"再者，Linux 讓你選擇你需要什麼與不要什麼，若你困擾於擺脫 Live Messenger、"
"Windows 更新通知，或者惱人的 Office 迴紋針小幫手，你將會發現 Linux 的清新感。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:60
msgid "Security"
msgstr "安全"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:62
msgid ""
"Forget expensive and restrictive anti-virus, anti-spyware, anti-anything and "
"anti-everything. Linux is very, very secure."
msgstr ""
"忘掉昂貴且有時效性的防毒、反間諜、防任何、防所有的軟體吧。Linux 非常、非常的"
"安全。"

#. translators: If you don't know of a link replacement in your languge, just leave the link as it is
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:64
msgid ""
"It is often difficult for Windows users to believe that there are <em>no "
"spyware nor viruses</em> under Linux &mdash; <a href=\"http://linuxmafia.com/"
"~rick/faq/index.php?page=virus#virus\">but it's true</a>. Malicious programs "
"have a hard time doing anything at all in a well-built system."
msgstr ""
"通常對 Windows 使用者而言難以相信的是：Linux 底下<em>沒有間諜軟體或病毒</em> "
"&mdash; <a href=\"http://linuxmafia.com/~rick/faq/index.php?page=virus#virus"
"\">但這是真的</a>。可疑軟體對精心打造的系統束手無策。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:65
msgid "Regular, easy software updates will keep everyone entirely safe."
msgstr "按時而簡單的軟體更新會保持所有人非常安全。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:69
msgid "Support"
msgstr "支援"

#. translators: The first %s represents the URL to the "More" page and seconds %s represents the title of the page "More" in your language
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:72
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Linux benefits from a great sense of community whose friendliness will "
"surprise you. If you try to do something complicated but can't succeed, "
"there are a lot of people around to help you out. Our \"<a href=\"%s\">%s</a>"
"\" page gives a few pointers."
msgstr ""
"Linux 裨益於廣大且友善程度令人驚異的社群。當你想做些複雜的事情卻無法達成時，"
"群眾將不吝於伸出援手幫助你。我們的「<a href=\"%s\">%s</a>」頁面提供一點方向。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:73
msgid ""
"The companies behind the main GNU/Linux distributions, such as <a href="
"\"http://www.canonical.com/\">Canonical</a> and <a href=\"http://www.redhat."
"com/\">Red Hat</a>, also provide expert commercial support."
msgstr ""
"主流的 GNU/Linux 散佈版背後的公司。如 <a href=\"http://www.canonical.com/"
"\">Canonical 科能</a> 和 <a href=\"http://www.redhat.com/\">Red Hat 紅帽</a> "
"也提供專業的商業支援。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:82
msgid "What is mostly the same in Linux"
msgstr "Linux 裡哪些是幾乎一樣的"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:84
msgid ""
"Fundamentally, everyday users will find GNU/Linux similar in use to Windows "
"or Mac OSX."
msgstr ""
"基本上，日常使用者會發現使用 GNU/Linux 與 Windows 或 Mac OSX 的差異不大。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:87
msgid "General set-up"
msgstr "一般安裝"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:89
msgid ""
"If you still believe Linux is controlled with code and command-line, you "
"should update your views!"
msgstr ""
"倘若你仍然堅信 Linux 必須從程式碼或命令列才能操作，那你應該更新一下你的觀點"
"了！"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:90
msgid ""
"Just like Windows, Linux has to boot when you switch your computer on, and "
"then you use programs in it to do different things. The taskbar and layout "
"of applications will feel familiar to Windows or Mac OS users."
msgstr ""
"就像 Windows一樣，Linux 必須在你開啟電腦時啟動，然後你能使用它提供的軟體做各"
"式各樣的事情。工作列以及程式畫面的佈局都令 Windows 或 Mac OS 使用者能感到熟"
"悉。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:94
msgid "Web browsing and common tasks"
msgstr "網路瀏覽與一般事務"

#. translators: use localized Firefox landing page if possible
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:97
msgid ""
"The Web looks just the same when viewed with Linux (in fact you can browse "
"the Web with the same program if you already use <a href=\"http://www."
"getfirefox.com/\">Firefox</a> or <a href=\"http://www.google.com/chrome/"
"\">Google Chrome</a>). And of course, you can go through your picture and "
"music collection all the same. Files and folders are navigated with a file "
"manager like Windows Explorer."
msgstr ""
"在 Linux 上看到的網頁和 Windows 下完全相同(事實上你可以選擇繼續使用你已經在使"
"用的軟體如 <a href=\"http://www.getfirefox.com/\">Firefox</a> 或者 <a href="
"\"http://www.google.com/chrome/\">Google Chrome</a>)。當然，你也可以像在 "
"Windows 下一樣查看你的照片，享受你的音樂。檔案和資料夾的管理和 Windows 下的 "
"Explorer 非常相似。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:106
msgid "What is not as good in Linux"
msgstr "Linux 還有哪裡不夠好"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:109
msgid "Driver support"
msgstr "驅動程式支援"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:111
msgid ""
"Manufacturers of computer hardware don't always (yet) release drivers for "
"Linux or publicize full specifications."
msgstr ""
"電腦硬體製造商 (還) 並不總是釋出 Linux 專用的驅動程式或者公布所有的規格特性。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:112
msgid ""
"So, drivers are sometimes unavailable for the most recent high-end graphics "
"cards &mdash; some are reverse-engineered from Windows drivers by "
"volunteers. Some are also released free of charge, but under restrictive "
"licenses."
msgstr ""
"所以，有些高階顯示卡的驅動程式可能會無法即時提供 &mdash; 有些是由志工對 "
"Windows 的驅動程式進行逆向工程而得。而有些則是驅動程式則是只能在受限的條款下"
"免費使用。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:113
msgid "Sadly, the same problem occurs with many low-end WiFi cards."
msgstr "悲傷的是，同樣的問題也發生在很多低階的 WiFi 介面卡。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:114
msgid ""
"However, the vast majority of computers with standard hardware work out of "
"the box with main Linux distributions. Common hardware such as USB keys or "
"photo cameras never are a problem."
msgstr ""
"不過，大多數的主流的 Linux 散佈版都可以在多數使用常見硬體的電腦上開箱即用。常"
"見的硬體，像是多數的USB裝置或是相機都不會是個問題。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:118
msgid "DVDs, restricted formats"
msgstr "DVD 受限制的格式"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:120
msgid ""
"Many multimedia formats in use are proprietary and not openly specified; "
"this means, broadly speaking, that Linux programmers have to find out how to "
"read them without any help from the format designers."
msgstr ""
"有為數不少的多媒體格式是受著作權限制，不完全公開的；所以 Linux 的開發者們通常"
"都必須在沒有原設計者的幫忙下找出如何讀取它們的方法。"

#. translators: Please choose the wording of the DRM acronym according to the FSF terminology
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:122
msgid ""
"This might lead you to circumvent the restrictions in some DVDs and the "
"<abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions Management\">DRM</abbr> in some music "
"files, even if you purchased them in full legality, to be make them work "
"under Linux. Unfortunately, depending on where you live, <em>such "
"circumvention processes may be illegal</em> even if you purchased your media "
"entirely legally."
msgstr ""
"這可能導致，即便你已經合法的購買了那些有<abbr title=\"Digital Restrictions "
"Management\">數位內容權利管理</abbr>的 DVD 或是音樂檔案，卻仍不得不繞過一些限"
"制以讓它們在 Linux 底下運作。不幸的是，在部份地區，<em>這些繞過限制的行為可能"
"是不合法的</em>，即使你已經完全合法的購買它們。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:123
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:136
msgid "Read more in our Linux FAQ:"
msgstr "到我們的 Linux FAQ 深入瞭解："

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:125
#: lib/views/linux.linux_faq.php:52 lib/views/linux.linux_faq.php:262
msgid "Can I play my DVDs and MP3s under GNU/Linux?"
msgstr "我可以在 GNU/Linux 上播放 DVD 和 MP3 嗎？"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:131
msgid "Gaming"
msgstr "遊戲"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:133
msgid ""
"Hard-core computer gamers, you might find that the Linux gaming world is "
"less professional and out-of-the-box than under Windows: the large game "
"developing companies are only slowly getting interested in the free software "
"world, which means that many well-known titles do not work on Linux, or need "
"special restrictive emulators to work."
msgstr ""
"重度玩家或許會發現 Linux 的遊戲世界比 Windows下更不需要專業，而且通常是隨開即"
"用的：大型遊戲開發商目前才慢慢向自由軟體世界展項興趣，換言之。就是許多有名的"
"大作在 Linux 下無法執行，或者需要很受限的模擬器才能執行。"

#. translators: use localised link if possible, and contact us if you know better resources
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:135
msgid ""
"There is a very active free software game development community though, and "
"they have produced quite a few high-quality games, both 2D and 3D, that are "
"free software. You can head to the <a href=\"http://ubuntuforums.org/"
"forumdisplay.php?f=93\">Ubuntu gaming forum</a> to find more information."
msgstr ""
"但仍然有一群積極的開發者們努力不懈的開發高品質的遊戲，不論是 2D 或 3D 的都"
"有，最重要的是，它們都是自由軟體！你可以前往<a href=\"http://ubuntuforums."
"org/forumdisplay.php?f=93\">Ubuntu 遊戲論壇</a>獲得更多資訊。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:138
#: lib/views/linux.linux_faq.php:53 lib/views/linux.linux_faq.php:282
msgid "Can I play popular 3D games under GNU/Linux?"
msgstr "我可以在 GNU/Linux 上玩流行的 3D 遊戲嗎？"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:144
msgid "Hibernating"
msgstr "讓電腦進入休眠狀態"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:146
msgid ""
"Because of the driver issues above, hibernating is not always reliable. The "
"most common occurrence is the loss of WiFi connection after hibernating on "
"laptops whose hardware drivers are not free."
msgstr ""
"因為以上的驅動程式問題，休眠並非總是可靠的。最常見的問題出現在 WiFi 在休眠回"
"復後失去連線，肇因於此硬體驅動程式並非自由的。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:155
msgid "Conclusion"
msgstr "總結"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:157
msgid ""
"Whether you are going to enjoy Linux depends mostly on what you expect from "
"it."
msgstr "你是否能享受 Linux 的樂趣取決於你對它的期待。"

#. translators: Use a localised version of the "Linux is Not Windows" article if possible. The following page contains links to localised versions: http://geekblog.oneandoneis2.org/index.php/2005/12/31/derived_works_aamp_translations
#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:162
msgid ""
"If you wish Linux to be just exactly like Windows, you will probably be "
"disappointed. GNU/Linux is built by people who simply <a href=\"http://linux."
"oneandoneis2.org/LNW.htm\">wish it to be different</a>. In the free software "
"community, members have different visions of what makes an ideal operating "
"system. These differences lead to variety, which is what makes Linux so "
"special and interesting."
msgstr ""
"倘若你期望 Linux 完全跟 Windows 一樣，那你可能感到失望，GNU/Linux 是由單純希"
"望它<a href=\"http://linux.oneandoneis2.org/LNW.htm\">不一樣</a>的人建造的。"
"在自由軟體社群裡，成員對一個理想的作業系統有不同的見解，而這些不同造成了差異"
"性，也讓 Linux 變的如此特別而有趣。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:165
msgid ""
"Your freedom matters. Thousands in communities and companies work to build "
"software on which you may exert this freedom. Using GNU/Linux is the easiest "
"way to do so fully."
msgstr ""
"我們在意你的自由，數以千計的社群與公司致力於建構能讓你投注自由的軟體。而使用 "
"GNU/Linux 是能完整實現他最輕鬆的途徑。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:168
msgid ""
"It's fun! Not having to worry about spyware, viruses, program registrations, "
"demos that expire, or finding software that is really free as in freedom, "
"makes using a computer suddenly very enjoyable."
msgstr ""
"超棒的！不需要擔心間諜軟體、病毒、軟體註冊、或試用過期，直到發現真的是自由使"
"用的軟體，讓用電腦的時光豁然開朗。"

#: lib/views/switch_to_linux.from_windows_to_linux.php:172
msgid ""
"We hope you'll switch soon. There's a large community waiting, and no one in "
"it asking you to &quot;sign up, purchase and register&quot;."
msgstr ""
"我們由衷希望你能快速轉換，有龐大的社群在等待著，而且不會有人要求你&quot;註"
"冊、購買、與登錄&quot;。"

#: lib/views/linux.linux_faq.php:16
